		"description": "<p>Those who would think that one trained in artifice is diminished if left in the wilds should beware your ingenuity. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence or Wisdom score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>While wearing wooden armor created with the benefits of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-feats.Item.vyT4fTNAPXmyRo7R]{Sylvan Constructor} feat, if you wild shape into a plant shape, the armor molds around the new form and you either use the armor&rsquo;s AC bonus or the new form&rsquo;s whichever is greater.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with jeweler&rsquo;s tools.</li>\n<li>You can create spell grenades using semi-precious stones and jeweler's tools. Doing so requires a semi-precious stone with a value of 10 x the spell&rsquo;s level in gold pieces and 10 minutes to cast a druid spell with a circular, spherical, or cubic area into the stone. The stone remains imbued with the spell for 8 hours. During that time, you can throw the stone as an action. Upon striking a target or the ground, the stone detonates, destroying the stone, dealing 2d6 piercing damage in a 10-foot radius and casting the imbued spell at its point of impact.</li>\n</ul>",
